Number 1,493 of 5,000 Mowrey Gun Works Bicentennial replica of the Allen (Ethan) & Thurber Plains Rifle in 50 caliber.  Mowrey did things only one way and that was the best. Stock is northern cherry, brass furniture and action, German silver blade sight and heavy barrel. Weighs 10 pounds and well balanced.

50 Caliber Charge: 125 grains of FFg black powder should produce a muzzle energy of 1,985 pound feet and energy of 2,300 feet per second.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Troy 11" Alpha rail - for carbine length gas system
postcontent:
This is a sweet Troy lightweight Aluminum Free Float Rail with an integrated, folding front sight. I purchased this used and got a great deal at $190 (they usually retail for $255). The previous owner used a dremel on the INSIDE of the front end to try and get a can to fit underneath on a SBR (see pic). These marks are purely cosmetic, have no functional impact, and I planned to just hit it with a quick spray of hi-temp black spray paint to cover the exposed Aluminum. 

The outside of the rail system doesn't have a single mark on it and is in like new condition. It comes in original box with all instructions, tools, and three modular rail sections to mount anywhere you want on the handguard.

My problem is that my upper has a mid length (9") gas system. I thought since my factory handguards were 9", that this 11" rail would work fine. Unfortunately, the position of the gas block interferes with the folding sight. If you have a standard 7" gas system, this is the handguard for you.

I like this rail so much, that I am going to spend $270 to buy the 13" version that fits mid length rifles (I'll have to buy a new one). However, I've got to get some of my money back out of this one in order to afford it. I'll take a loss of $10 plus the $8 I spent on shipping and will sell for $180. Im located in Midtown Nashville and will travel short distances or ship.
